commitResults.messageBody:
Initially, with the way the argument tokenizer worked,
it needed every prefix to have an argument following it.

With `ArgumentTokenizer::isFlagPresent` added in the previous commit,
we can now check for flags (prefixes w/o arguments) directly.

This means that `ls -A` works correctly.
